India’s women healthier, wealthier and connected

The findings of the fourth National Family Health Survey (NFHS), released by the ministry of health, has some good news on women’s well-being in the country. They are more empowered when it comes to decision-making, health issues, money matters, and education than they were a decade before. Here’s more... 
